Hi Myrna!

Yes, you are correct in thinking that the `textExtraction` method is needed. I'm not sure of the order of your table cells, but lets assume it's the first column (column zero for a zero-based index).

```javascript
// Define a custom text extraction function for each column
// by default, the plugin uses `$(node).text()`
textExtraction: {
	0: function(node) {
		return $(node).find('span:not(.crossgenus)').text().replace(/\'/g,'');
	}
}
```

This function gets all of the text from inside of the spans, except the cross genus span. If you need to see another example, see [this demo](http://mottie.github.com/tablesorter/docs/example-option-text-extraction.html).

Please note that this method will only work with the updated tablesorter plugin available here, the original tablesorter plugin did not include a textExtraction method that worked with individual columns.

