@saratlingamarla I appreciate the effort to implement this and open the PR, but there do seem to be a few issues with it.

1. The TravisCI tests [all failed](https://travis-ci.org/jantman/awslimitchecker/builds/271061435). That's unrelated to your changes; a new release of tox broke them. I've [fixed](https://travis-ci.org/jantman/awslimitchecker/builds/271141183) that in a [commit](https://github.com/jantman/awslimitchecker/commit/1478955c571ebf6a6abd84d70c20852b22aa52f5) on the develop branch; if you could rebase on that, we should see more accurate test results for this branch.
2. I see that it doesn't have any tests at all. I know that a lot of people aren't familiar with pytest, so I try to assist when I can. However... (1) I'd appreciate it if you at least created the test template file, as described in the [Adding Services](http://awslimitchecker.readthedocs.io/en/latest/development.html#adding-new-services) section of the docs, and (2) Have you ever tried this code? I noticed a few pretty big omissions that I think would prevent it from running at all...

