I realise this is an almost year-old issue, but it's one of the top results when trying to get daphne working behind an nginx reverse proxy. I had issues as well, and the solution came from [this nginx doc page](http://nginx.org/en/docs/http/websocket.html).

Specifically, I had problems with having daphne serve all the content, and either HTTP or websockets would work, but not both. The relevant nginx config that solved it was, and note particularly the `connection_upgrade` mapping:
```
map $http_upgrade $connection_upgrade {
	default   upgrade;
	''        close;
}
upstream django {
	server 127.0.0.1:9000;
	keepalive 16;
}

server {
	server_name <deleted>.com;
        location / {
                    proxy_pass              http://django;
		    proxy_http_version  1.1;
                    proxy_set_header    Host $host;
		    proxy_set_header    Upgrade $http_upgrade;
		    proxy_set_header        Connection $connection_upgrade;
                    proxy_set_header        X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
                    proxy_set_header        X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
                    proxy_set_header        X-Forwarded-Host $server_name;
        }
}

